    "summary": "The user describes sudden, intense headache and facial drooping, asking if it could be a migraine and if they can take sumatriptan. The assistant repeatedly and correctly identifies these as red-flag symptoms of a stroke and urgently directs the user to seek emergency medical services (911/ER) while advising against self-medication.",
